.TH CLKMGR_PROXY "8" "June 2025" "clkmgr_proxy"
.SH NAME
clkmgr_proxy \- Clock Manager proxy service
.SH SYNOPSIS
clkmgr_proxy [ OPTIONS ] [ -f FILE ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Clock Manager proxy service is a user-space service that acts as a proxy for
clock management operations on a system. It facilitates communication between
the clock synchronization services and client applications. This service is
typically used in environments that require precise clock synchronization and
management, such as in time-sensitive networking or industrial automation systems.
The configuration of the proxy service can be configured using a JSON configuration
file, as described in \fBclkmgr_proxy_cfg\fR(5).
.SH OPTIONS
.HP
\fB\-f\fR [file] Read configuration from 'file'
.HP
\fB\-a\fR <0|1> Open message queue in access all mode
.IP
0: disable(default), 1: enable
.HP
\fB\-l\fR <lvl> Set log level
.IP
0: ERROR, 1: INFO(default), 2: DEBUG, 3: TRACE
.HP
\fB\-q\fR <0|1> Enable or disable quiet mode
.IP
0: disable, 1: enable
.HP
\fB\-s\fR <0|1> Enable or disable use of system logging
.IP
0: disable, 1: enable
.TP
\fB\-v\fR
Show version
.TP
\fB\-h\fR
Show help message
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\fBclkmgr_proxy_cfg\fR(5)
